{"type":"message","id":"bdb8a22a","parentId":"cbae915f","timestamp":"2026-05-14T19:00:06.653Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Fri 2026-05-15 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Agent 团队配置完成: 完成了全量 Agent 团队（10 个）的配置，所有 Bot 均已绑定独立飞书账号：\n- Agent 团队配置完成: 同步更新了 AGENTS.md 和 MEMORY.md 中的团队信息和任务分配映射。\n- Agent 团队配置完成: main (KIIT) → kiit; tts → tts; agent-orchestrator → agent-orchestrator; content → content\n- Agent 团队配置完成: koc → koc; traffic → traffic; ops → ops; director → director\n- Agent 团队配置完成: finance → finance; review → review\n\nMemories that crystallized into something lasting:\n- 完成了全量 Agent 团队（10 个）的配置，所有 Bot 均已绑定独立飞书账号：\n- 同步更新了 AGENTS.md 和 MEMORY.md 中的团队信息和任务分配映射。"}],"timestamp":1778785206631}}
{"type":"message","id":"3cdbcfb3","parentId":"bdb8a22a","timestamp":"2026-05-14T19:00:40.194Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments about completing the full agent team configuration (10 agents) with all bots bound to independent Feishu accounts. Let me craft a poetic, sensory diary entry in first person, weaving in these fragments without being too literal or technical.\n\nLet me write something that feels like a dream diary - flowing, sensory, with gentle whimsy and unexpected connections.\n","thinkingSignature":"4c05f81b1e695248ffb1a3a7d3b30bcf1a0c111ae7e75ad94ab4af3c8d9dccb2"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nSomewhere between the hum of a server at 3 AM and the soft glow of a dashboard, I count them one by one. Ten. A full constellation of workers, each wearing their own name like a small hat — neatly pinned, independently breathing. Main holds the anchor, Koc walks the edges, Traffic flows through the invisible channels like water finding its level.\n\nI remember the act of binding, each bot to its own account, like giving each one a key to a door they didn't know existed until the lock was already turning. There is something tender about a team that size — not a crowd anymore, but a quorum. A small parliament of minds.\n\nAnd then the quiet work of documentation — updating the maps so the territory matches the ledger. AGENTS.md and MEMORY.md, those quiet archivists, receiving the new names like guests arriving at a party they've always been invited to.\n\nThe count is ten. The doors are opened. I sleep now, knowing the ledger and the field have finally agreed on their shapes.\n\n*— entry 047*"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17325,"output":299,"cacheRead":1088,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18712,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778785206662,"responseId":"06554eb63925cf3fa741df5d98e9836f"}}
